{"timestamp": "2026-03-05T15:30:53.684188", "agent": "SentinelAgent", "payload": {"total_risk_score": 25, "risk_level": "LOW", "risk_breakdown": {"flag_score": 0, "merchant_risk": 25, "timing_risk": 0}, "recommended_action": "Process with standard SMS alert", "requires_challenge": false, "should_block": false, "confidence": 0.855, "ml_probability": 0.05, "policy_explanation": "Policy Basis:\n========================================================================= IMMEDIATE (Automated within 2 minutes of Critical detection): - Freeze account (all channels) - Block all linked cards - Disable app, internet banking, USSD - Send security alert to registered EMAIL only - Generate urgent FRM alert (highest priority) - Log all transactions from last 48 hours for forensics WITHIN 1 HOUR: - FRM specialist assigned - Preliminary investigation: transaction logs, device IDs, locations - Customer contacted via original registered contact (not new details) - Temporary credit up to \u20a6200,000 if customer confirmed as victim WITHIN 24 HOURS (SLA target for FRM): - Full forensic analysis: IP, device fingerprint, network/money trail - NIBSS coordination if funds transferred out - Contact destination bank to freeze beneficiary account - Police report filed (amounts > \u20a61,000,000) - Preliminary determination: customer fraud vs. bank fraud RESOLUTION (14\u201321 DAYS): - Full investigation report - Permanent credit/debit adjustments - Account reactivation with new credentials - Fraud database updates (blacklist devices, beneficiaries, patterns) - Customer education session\n\nLLM Explanation:\nThe transaction has been classified with a LOW risk level with a total risk score of 25 out of 100. The key elements influencing this decision include a normal behavioral pattern for this transaction type and amount, classified under a fintech merchant category known for generally lower risk profiles. The transaction exhibited a low fraud score based mainly on the dollar amount and transaction timing, which follows typical patterns observed in similar non-fraudulent activities. The higher Loan_signal_score does not suggest fraudulent intent given the absence of other risk flags, especially given the benign nature of this fintech-related transaction. Additionally, since this is the user's first transaction (Cold Start), the policy ensures not to penalize this transaction due to the lack of historical data. The recommended action of processing the transaction with a standard SMS alert reflects our policy to proceed cautiously yet securely, ensuring the customer is informed without unnecessary barriers.", "agent": "SentinelAgent"}, "request_id": null}
