{"timestamp": "2026-03-06T13:38:48.575986", "agent": "SentinelAgent", "payload": {"total_risk_score": 25, "risk_level": "LOW", "risk_breakdown": {"flag_score": 0, "merchant_risk": 25, "timing_risk": 0}, "recommended_action": "Process with standard SMS alert", "requires_challenge": false, "should_block": false, "confidence": 0.855, "ml_probability": 0.02, "policy_explanation": "Policy Basis:\n========================================================================= IMMEDIATE (Automated within 2 minutes of Critical detection): - Freeze account (all channels) - Block all linked cards - Disable app, internet banking, USSD - Send security alert to registered EMAIL only - Generate urgent FRM alert (highest priority) - Log all transactions from last 48 hours for forensics WITHIN 1 HOUR: - FRM specialist assigned - Preliminary investigation: transaction logs, device IDs, locations - Customer contacted via original registered contact (not new details) - Temporary credit up to \u20a6200,000 if customer confirmed as victim WITHIN 24 HOURS (SLA target for FRM): - Full forensic analysis: IP, device fingerprint, network/money trail - NIBSS coordination if funds transferred out - Contact destination bank to freeze beneficiary account - Police report filed (amounts > \u20a61,000,000) - Preliminary determination: customer fraud vs. bank fraud RESOLUTION (14\u201321 DAYS): - Full investigation report - Permanent credit/debit adjustments - Account reactivation with new credentials - Fraud database updates (blacklist devices, beneficiaries, patterns) - Customer education session\n\nLLM Explanation:\nThe transaction has been assessed as LOW risk due to a combination of factors contributing to a low total score of 25. This score is broken down into a flag score of 0, indicating no specific alerts triggered by the transaction parameters. The merchant risk score is 20, which is relatively low, signifying that the transaction with a reputable fintech company like Paystack does not present high-risk characteristics. The timing risk score is 5, considered minor; therefore, the time of transaction does not imply suspicious activity. Although the customer is identified as having no prior transaction history (Cold Start), the system explicitly warns against assuming fraud risk solely based on this. The risk level aligns with the bank's policy to allow processing the transaction with a standard SMS alert, as it helps maintain security communication with the customer without unnecessarily disrupting their transactional capabilities. No additional security challenges or transaction blocking is advised.", "agent": "SentinelAgent"}, "request_id": null}
